MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

DIAGNOSIS: Phase 0g's wholesale-copy of lucebox's gated_delta_net.cu +
ssm-conv.cu introduced kernel template instantiations whose nbytes_shared
exceeds Pascal sm_61's 48 KB per-block shared memory limit. cudaFuncSetAttribute
in mmq.cuh:3955 (CUDA_SET_SHARED_MEMORY_LIMIT) failed with 'illegal memory
access' at module init.

EMPIRICAL EVIDENCE:
  - Production llama-server (Sakatard fork @ f5fd4ecad, no lucebox): runs
    fine at 18.48 tok/s decode on P40 (Phase 0c bench)
  - Phase 0g+0h binary with lucebox kernels: crashes mmq.cuh on first decode
  - LLAMA_DFLASH=OFF didn't help — same crash → not dflash linkage related
  - Revert ggml-cuda kernels to feature/mtp-turboquant-integration HEAD
    → builds + runs clean at 21.62 tok/s decode, 66% MTP draft acceptance

KEEP:
  - ggml/include/ggml.h: GGML_TYPE_TQ3_0 stub + 3 tree-op decls
  - ggml/src/ggml.c: 3 tree-op wrapper impls (set src[2/6/7] on result tensor)
  - These compile cleanly + don't break Pascal; tree-mode silently disabled
    at runtime since reverted CUDA kernels don't check src[2/6/7].

PHASE 0h v2 PIVOT: for proper tree-mode support, need surgical kernel diff
merge (~1-2 days of careful CUDA work) NOT wholesale copy. Deferred to v3.
v0 ship continues with non-tree MTP self-spec-decode (Phase 0c-proven).

